HEADWORD: Outlying
<hw>Out"ly`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Lying or being at a
distance from the central part, or the main body; being on, or beyond,
the frontier; exterior; remote; detached.</def>⟦br⟧
